Package: scrolllock-led-daemon
Version: 1.0.0-1
Architecture: all
Maintainer: Alan Santos <alan.profissional.dev@gmail.com>
Installed-Size: 51
Depends: python3:any, python3-evdev
Section: utils
Priority: optional
Homepage: https://github.com/alan-n7x/scrolllock-led-daemon
Description: Daemon that synchronizes the Scroll Lock key with the keyboard LED on Linux.
 Scroll Lock LED Daemon listens for a key press and toggles the corresponding
 keyboard LED. It runs as a background service managed by systemd, auto-detects
 the keyboard, and supports configurable keys and LEDs. Features include:
  - Auto-detects keyboard and Scroll Lock LED
  - Listens for key presses and toggles the LED
  - Runs as a systemd service (Type=notify)
  - Auto-reconnects if the keyboard is disconnected
  - One-shot mode: --set on/off and --toggle for scripts
  - Configuration file support
